headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam made a key 3-pointer late in the fourth quarter and finished with 20 points, nine rebounds and five assists to help the Indiana Pacers beat the reeling Atlanta Hawks 132-127 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Pascal Siakam hits late 3-pointer as the Pacers hang on to beat the Hawks, 132-127

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 22 points and John Collins added 19 to help the Utah Jazz snap an eight-game losing streak with a 113-99 victory over the Orlando Magic on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton scores 22 points and Jazz beat Magic 113-99 to snap 8-game losing streak

headlines.description: — Nicola Jokic had 28 points, 17 assists and 13 rebounds for his 22nd triple-double of the season to help the Denver Nuggets beat the Charlotte Hornets 107-104 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has 28 points, 17 assists and 13 rebounds to lead the Nuggets past the Hornets, 107-104.

headlines.description: — Ziaire Williams had 21 points, D’Angelo Russell added 18 and the Brooklyn Nets won consecutive games for the first time since November with a 110-98 victory over the short-handed Houston Rockets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets win consecutive games for 1st time since November with 110-98 victory over Rockets

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored a season-high 31 points and the Washington Wizards beat the short-handed Minnesota Timberwolves 105-103 on Saturday night to end a 16-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards beat Timberwolves 105-103 to end 16-game losing streak

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Aaron Wiggins had a career-high 41 points and 14 rebounds, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rolled past the Sacramento Kings 144-110 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins scores career-high 41 and Thunder outrebound Kings 70-37 in 144-110 rout

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 33 points, 12 assists and 11 rebounds in his 10th triple-double of the season, enjoying another memorable night at Madison Square Garden and leading the Los Angeles Lakers to a 128-112 victory over the New York Knicks on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James has a triple-double and another win at Madison Square Garden as Lakers beat Knicks

events.name: Miami Heat at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo hit a 19-foot jumper as time expired to cap a 30-point, 13-rebound outing and give the Miami Heat a 105-103 victory over San Antonio on Saturday night with Spurs star <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo hits 19-footer at buzzer to cap 30-point outing in Heat's 105-103 win over Spurs

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had 24 points on 11-of-12 shooting against his former team and the Portland Trail Blazers opened a two-game set against the Phoenix Suns with a 127-108 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Deandre Ayton leads Trail Blazers to 127-108 victory over Suns in opener of 2-game set
